            <div class="glossary-grid">
                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">SST (Sea Surface Temperature)</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">SSTï¼ˆæµ·æ°´æ¸©ï¼‰</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term-en" data-lang="ja">Sea Surface Temperature</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">The temperature of the ocean's surface layer, typically measured by satellites. This site uses NASA MUR SST data at 1km resolution.</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">æµ·é¢ä»˜è¿‘ã®æ°´æ¸©ã€‚è¡›æ˜Ÿã«ã‚ˆã£ã¦è¦³æ¸¬ã•ã‚Œã‚‹ã€‚ã“ã®ã‚µã‚¤ãƒˆã§ã¯NASA MUR SSTã®1kmè§£åƒåº¦ãƒ‡ãƒ¼ã‚¿ã‚’ä½¿ç”¨ã€‚</p>
                </div>

                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">MMM (Maximum Monthly Mean)</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">MMMï¼ˆæœˆåˆ¥æœ€é«˜å¹³å‡æ°´æ¸©ï¼‰</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term-en" data-lang="ja">Maximum Monthly Mean</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">The highest monthly average SST at a location, calculated from historical data. Used as the baseline for measuring thermal stress. Sesoko: 29.0â„ƒ, Manza: 29.0â„ƒ.</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">ã‚ã‚‹åœ°ç‚¹ã«ãŠã‘ã‚‹æœˆå¹³å‡æµ·æ°´æ¸©ã®å¹´é–“æœ€é«˜å€¤ã€‚éå»ã®ãƒ‡ãƒ¼ã‚¿ã‹ã‚‰ç®—å‡ºã•ã‚Œã€ç†±ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹ã®åŸºæº–å€¤ã¨ãªã‚‹ã€‚ç€¬åº•ï¼š29.0â„ƒã€ä¸‡åº§ï¼š29.0â„ƒã€‚</p>
                </div>

                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">DHW (Degree Heating Weeks)</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">DHWï¼ˆç†±ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹æŒ‡æ¨™ï¼‰</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term-en" data-lang="ja">Degree Heating Weeks</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">A measure of accumulated heat stress. Calculated by summing temperatures exceeding MMM+1â„ƒ over the past 12 weeks. DHW â‰¥ 4: bleaching likely. DHW â‰¥ 8: severe bleaching and mortality likely.</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">è“„ç©ã•ã‚ŒãŸç†±ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹ã®æŒ‡æ¨™ã€‚éå»12é€±é–“ã§MMM+1â„ƒã‚’è¶…ãˆãŸæ°´æ¸©ã®ç´¯ç©å€¤ã€‚DHW 4ä»¥ä¸Šã§ç™½åŒ–ã®å¯èƒ½æ€§ã€8ä»¥ä¸Šã§å¤§è¦æ¨¡ç™½åŒ–ãƒ»æ­»äº¡ã®å¯èƒ½æ€§ã€‚</p>
                    <p class="glossary-note" data-lang="en">Note: Satellite DHW tends to overestimate compared to in-situ measurements (2-3x higher in Sesoko studies).</p>
                    <p class="glossary-note" data-lang="ja">æ³¨ï¼šè¡›æ˜ŸDHWã¯ç¾åœ°è¦³æ¸¬ã‚ˆã‚Š2ã€œ3å€é«˜ãå‡ºã‚‹å‚¾å‘ãŒã‚ã‚‹ï¼ˆç€¬åº•ã®ç ”ç©¶ã«ã‚ˆã‚‹ï¼‰ã€‚</p>
                </div>

                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">Coral Bleaching</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">ã‚µãƒ³ã‚´ã®ç™½åŒ–</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">When stressed by high temperatures, corals expel their symbiotic algae (zooxanthellae), losing their color and primary energy source. Prolonged bleaching leads to mortality.</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">é«˜æ°´æ¸©ãªã©ã®ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹ã«ã‚ˆã‚Šã€ã‚µãƒ³ã‚´ãŒå…±ç”Ÿè—»ï¼ˆè¤è™«è—»ï¼‰ã‚’æ”¾å‡ºã™ã‚‹ç¾è±¡ã€‚è‰²ãŒç™½ããªã‚Šã€ä¸»è¦ãªã‚¨ãƒãƒ«ã‚®ãƒ¼æºã‚’å¤±ã†ã€‚é•·æœŸåŒ–ã™ã‚‹ã¨æ­»äº¡ã«è‡³ã‚‹ã€‚</p>
                </div>

                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">Bleaching Alert Levels</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">ç™½åŒ–è­¦å ±ãƒ¬ãƒ™ãƒ«</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">NOAA's classification system based on thermal stress:</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">NOAAã«ã‚ˆã‚‹ç†±ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹ã®åˆ†é¡ï¼š</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def">
                        <span data-lang="en">â€¢ No Stress: SST below MMM<br>â€¢ Watch: SST exceeds MMM<br>â€¢ Warning: DHW > 0<br>â€¢ Alert Level 1: DHW â‰¥ 4<br>â€¢ Alert Level 2: DHW â‰¥ 8</span>
                        <span data-lang="ja">ãƒ»ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹ãªã—ï¼šSSTãŒMMMæœªæº€<br>ãƒ»æ³¨æ„ï¼šSSTãŒMMMã‚’è¶…é<br>ãƒ»è­¦æˆ’ï¼šDHWãŒ0ã‚’è¶…é<br>ãƒ»è­¦å ±ãƒ¬ãƒ™ãƒ«1ï¼šDHW 4ä»¥ä¸Š<br>ãƒ»è­¦å ±ãƒ¬ãƒ™ãƒ«2ï¼šDHW 8ä»¥ä¸Š</span>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">Thermal History</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">ç†±å±¥æ­´</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">The pattern of heat stress over multiple years. Research shows that corals exposed to moderate stress in one year may show increased short-term tolerance the following year.</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">è¤‡æ•°å¹´ã«ã‚ãŸã‚‹ç†±ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹ã®ãƒ‘ã‚¿ãƒ¼ãƒ³ã€‚ç ”ç©¶ã«ã‚ˆã‚‹ã¨ã€å‰å¹´ã«ä¸­ç¨‹åº¦ã®ã‚¹ãƒˆãƒ¬ã‚¹ã‚’çµŒé¨“ã—ãŸã‚µãƒ³ã‚´ã¯ã€ç¿Œå¹´ã«çŸ­æœŸçš„ãªè€ç†±æ€§ãŒå‘ä¸Šã™ã‚‹ã“ã¨ãŒã‚ã‚‹ã€‚</p>
                </div>

                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">NOAA Coral Reef Watch</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">NOAA Coral Reef Watch</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">A program by the U.S. National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration that provides global satellite monitoring of coral reef ecosystems and bleaching risk.</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">ç±³å›½æµ·æ´‹å¤§æ°—åºã«ã‚ˆã‚‹ãƒ—ãƒ­ã‚°ãƒ©ãƒ ã€‚è¡›æ˜Ÿãƒ‡ãƒ¼ã‚¿ã‚’ç”¨ã„ã¦ä¸–ç•Œã®ã‚µãƒ³ã‚´ç¤ç”Ÿæ…‹ç³»ã¨ç™½åŒ–ãƒªã‚¹ã‚¯ã‚’ãƒ¢ãƒ‹ã‚¿ãƒªãƒ³ã‚°ã€‚</p>
                </div>

                <div class="glossary-card">
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="en">Monitoring Sites 1000</div>
                    <div class="glossary-term" data-lang="ja">ãƒ¢ãƒ‹ã‚¿ãƒªãƒ³ã‚°ã‚µã‚¤ãƒˆ1000</div>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="en">A long-term ecological monitoring program by Japan's Ministry of the Environment, tracking biodiversity changes at 1,000 sites across Japan, including coral reefs.</p>
                    <p class="glossary-def" data-lang="ja">ç’°å¢ƒçœã«ã‚ˆã‚‹é•·æœŸç”Ÿæ…‹ç³»ãƒ¢ãƒ‹ã‚¿ãƒªãƒ³ã‚°èª¿æŸ»ã€‚æ—¥æœ¬å…¨å›½ç´„1,000ç®‡æ‰€ã§ç”Ÿç‰©å¤šæ§˜æ€§ã®å¤‰åŒ–ã‚’è¿½è·¡ã€‚ã‚µãƒ³ã‚´ç¤ã‚‚å¯¾è±¡ã«å«ã¾ã‚Œã‚‹ã€‚</p>
